{{Quote|It's new Imperial scrip. You can only spend it on Imperial-held worlds and stations.|Bar patron at [[Mishra]]|<ref name="Dark Force Rising">''[[Dark Force Rising]]''</ref>}}
'''Military scrip''', also called simply '''scrip''' or '''Imperial scrip''', was currency issued to members of the [[Imperial Military/Legends|Imperial Military]]. It was an accepted medium of exchange throughout the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], and there were harsh punishments for not accepting Imperial currency, whether or not the credit was considered a good risk. It was interchangeable with [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] for a small fee.

Scrip was not accepted as valid currency outside of the Empire, whose influence had waned greatly in the time of the [[New Republic]]. Furthermore, there was no official rate of exchange, but unofficially there was a five to four Empire/Republic conversion rate, or five to three depending on whom you talked with.<ref name="Dark Force Rising" />

